    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="245"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hart</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 573, of February 25 last,
                    in regard to the complaint of the Swiss citizen, Roberto Beck, I inclose copy of
                    a memorandum<note n="a" xml:id="d245fna">Printed, <ref target="#pg_979">page
                            979</ref>.</note> left with me by the Swiss minister at this capital, in
                    which he asks this Government to make representations to the Colombian
                    Government, with a view to putting an end to the expropriation of Mr. Beck’s
                    mules, and to obtain compensation for the injuries already done to him.</p>
                <pb facs="0371" n="291" xml:id="pg_291"/>
                <p>The Department would be pleased to receive a more complete report regarding the
                    case and the action taken by you than that contained in your dispatch above
                    referred to.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
